---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Nathan Rasmussen and the custom design, prototyping, 3D printing, painting, finishing, and assembly work behind Nathan Rasmussen Design."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container about-grid">
      <figure class="about-media">
        <img
          src="/images/portfolio/nathan-deer.jpg"
          alt="Nathan with a custom deer display piece."
          width="1200"
          height="800"
        />
      </figure>
      <div class="stack">
        <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
        <h1>I enjoy turning ideas into physical objects.</h1>
        <p>
          What started as an interest in 3D printing quickly grew into a passion for designing
          and building custom pieces. Over the past several years I've created awards, display
          pieces, prototypes, and personal projects, combining digital design with hands-on
          fabrication and finishing.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background in physics and software development has shaped the way I approach
          every project. I enjoy breaking complex problems into manageable pieces, iterating
          on designs, and refining the details until the final result feels complete. Whether
          a project requires original CAD work, thoughtful adaptation, or simply careful
          craftsmanship, my focus is always on producing something I'd be proud to put my
          name on.
        </p>
        <p>
          From the first conversation through the final coat of paint, I enjoy every stage
          of the process. Seeing an idea become something you can hold in your hands is what
          keeps me coming back to the workshop.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
